io.github.utk003.util.data.collection.multi.set

Class MapBackedMultiSet<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • io.github.utk003.util.data.collection.multi.set.AbstractMultiSet<E>
        • io.github.utk003.util.data.collection.multi.set.MapBackedMultiSet<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - The class type of the elements contained in this MapBackedMultiSet
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    MultiSet<E>, Iterable<E>, Collection<E>

    public class MapBackedMultiSet<E>
extends AbstractMultiSet<E>
implements MultiSet<E>
    A Map-backed implementation of the MultiSet.

    This class uses a E-to-Integer map to keep track of multiple copies of an object being present in this multiset. The map itself is generic, so any class that implements Map can be provided into either of the two constructors.

    Since:
    2.1.0
    Version:
    June 11, 2021
    Author:
